title: Isao Takahata and His Tale of the Princess Kaguya
description:
I believe this is in 720p, please correct me if I am wrong.

From IMDB: A documentary about the making of The Tale of Princess Kaguya, Isao Takahata's first feature film for 14 years.

Audio: Japanese
Hard-coded Subtitles: English

My take: This is a great documentary that is very similar to The Kingdom of Dreams and Madness (a documentary about the making of Hayao Miyazaki's The Wind Rises). If you enjoyed the movie, The Tale of the Princess Kaguya, you will likely enjoy this documentary
